                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A woodblock printed study of acupuncture in kanbun by Hara Nan’yō with line illustrations, published in 1807 by the author and distributed for sale by Suharaya Anjirō of Mito and other commercial publishers from Osaka, Edo and Kyoto.                           
                        </summary>
                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_21">

                            <author key="person_114142765" source="VIAF">
                                <persName type="original" xml:lang="ja">原南陽</persName>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn">Hara Nan’yō</persName>
                                <note> Hara Nan’yō's (1753-1820) father was a doctor to the daimyo
                                    of Mito, and Hara studied obstetrics and other medical subjects
                                    in Kyoto; he subsequently spent some time in Edo in poverty
                                    until asked to treat the daimyo of Mito in his Edo residence.
                                    His treatment was successful and he was appointed as ne of the
                                    daimyo’s physicians, in which capacity he served successive
                                    daimyo for more than 30 years. He published a number of works
                                    and is particularly known for his Toridegusa とり でぐさ　which was
                                    published in 1811 and was the first work in Japan devoted to
                                    military medicine and hygiene.</note>
                            </author>

                            <respStmt>
                                <persName type="original" xml:lang="ja">須原家安次郎</persName>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn">Suharaya Anjirō</persName>
                                <resp>Distributor</resp>
                            </respStmt>

                      
                                <title type="original" xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">経穴彙解</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Keiketsu ikai</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="en" source="IANA">On acupuncture</title>

